{{Infobox organization | name = Malaysia Australia Business Council | type = [[Chamber of commerce]] | founded_date = 1986 | founder = YAM Tunku Dato' Seri Shahabuddin bin Tunku Besar Burhanuddin | location = [[Kuala Lumpur]] | key_people = Leigh Howard, Chairman | area_served = [[Malaysia]]-[[Australia]] | focus = Business advocacy, diplomatic relations | homepage = [http://www.mabc.org.my/ Malaysia Australia Business Council Official Website] | tax_exempt = yes | dissolved = | footnotes = }}
The '''Malaysia Australia Business Council''' (MABC) is a non-profit business chamber founded in 1986 with the aim of promoting the interests of its members based in [[Malaysia]] with business links to [[Australia]].<ref>http://www.mabc.org.my</ref> <ref>http://malaysia.highcommission.gov.au/klpr/trade_mabc.html</ref>
As an active business chamber, the council provides a forum for Malaysian and Australian linked businesses and business people. The MABC works closely with the governments of both countries and plays an active role in developing the bilateral relationship. It is led by an Executive Committee made up of prominent business people from both countries. It's co-patrons are the [[Mustapa Mohamed|Malaysian Minister of Trade & Industry]] and the Australian High Commissioner.
The MABC works closely with its sister organisation in Australia, the Australia Malaysia Business Council (AMBC).<ref>http://www.ambc.org.au/mabc/</ref>
In recent years the MABC has seen a growth in activity due to the signing of the Malaysia Australia Free Trade Agreement (MAFTA) which has resulted in increasing bilateral trade between the two countries.<ref>http://www.thestar.com.my/Business/Business-News/2015/06/24/More-Aussie-firms-choose-Msia-as-export-destination-says-MABC/?style=biz</ref>
