{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}} {{Use Irish English|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Ray O'Rourke | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Raymond Gabriel O'Rourke | birth_date = {{bya|1947|01}} | birth_place = [[County Leitrim]], Ireland | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | nationality = Irish | occupation = Businessman | title = Chairman and CEO, [[Laing O'Rourke]] | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = Founder and 55% owner of Laing O'Rourke | networth = €800 million (2015)<ref name="independent.ie"/> }}
'''Raymond Gabriel O'Rourke, KBE, HONFREng, C.Eng., FIEI, FICE''' (born January 1947)<ref name="bloomberg"/> is an Irish businessman, the chairman and CEO of the construction multinational [[Laing O'Rourke]].<ref name="independent.ie">{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/business/irish/rich-list-2015/profiles/ray-and-des-orourke-31046084.html|title=Ray and Des O'Rourke - Independent.ie|website=independent.ie|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref>
O'Rourke was born in January 1947.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/gy2eKnr5r3WUhci4dytAvB1kmpA/appointments|title=Raymond Gabriel O'ROURKE - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House)|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref> A native of [[County Leitrim]], Ireland,<ref name="independent.ie"/><ref name="scotsman.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/the-man-and-the-parliament-millions-1-893789|title=The man and the Parliament millions|website=scotsman.com|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref> he runs the privately owned Laing O'Rourke with his brother Des, and owns 55% of the company.<ref name="scotsman.com"/> O'Rourke "started as a 'pony boy' carrying muck out from under London as the Victoria Line was being constructed." His estimated net worth was €800 million as of 2015.<ref name="independent.ie"/>
He has honorary doctorates from the [[Dublin Institute of Technology]], and [[Queen's University, Belfast]].<ref name="bloomberg">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=28386148&privcapId=5481700|title=Ray G. O'Rourke: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=bloomberg.com|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref>
O'Rourke purchased the construction company '''Swift Structures''', owned by his brothers-in-law, Jim and Matt Halligan from County Mayo. He then called in the receivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/business/builder-orourke-buys-out-firm-of-family-rivals-26124380.html|title=Builder O'Rourke buys out firm of family rivals|website=independent.ie|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/the-man-and-the-parliament-millions-1-893789|title=The man and the Parliament millions|website=scotsman.com|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref> His son, Cathal, works for Laing O'Rourke.<ref name="independent.ie"/>
