'''''The Coming Jobs War''''' is a [[book]] by [[The Gallup Organization|Gallup]] Chairman [[Jim Clifton]].
Clifton claims that a lack of [[innovation]] is not the problem, but rather a lack of [[entrepreneurship]].
==Reviews== [[Deepak Chopra]] wrote that ''The Coming Jobs War'' is "excellent and timely"<ref>[http://businessjournal.gallup.com/content/147848/Coming-Jobs-War.aspx The Coming Jobs War] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120805042816/http://businessjournal.gallup.com/content/147848/Coming-Jobs-War.aspx |date=2012-08-05 }}</ref> and Charles M. Blow in the [[New York Times]] commenting the book is "fascinating - and frightening." <ref>{{cite web|title=For Jobs, It's War|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/17/opinion/blow-for-jobs-its-war.html|website=New York Times|publisher=www.nytimes.com|accessdate=29 December 2014}}</ref>
